part in the occu-</div><div class="t m56 x11 h4 y198d ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">pations and pleasures of </div><div class="t m56d xa4 h30 y1bdc ff6 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">heaven.&quot;—&quot;Testimonies to Ministers,&quot; </div><div class="t m580 x7f h4 ya65 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">p. 18. </div><div class="t m1d5 x5d h4 y38 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">8. </div><div class="t m740 x28 h4 y1a15 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">What importance does the apostle attach to the indwelling presence </div><div class="t m7ab x11 h4 y1926 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of the Holy Spirit? Rom. 8:9. </div><div class="t m9c1 x5d h4 y1a61 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">NOTE.—&quot;The Holy Spirit seeks to abide in each soul. If it is welcomed as </div><div class="t mfb x11 h4 y6bd ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">an honored guest, those who receive it will be made complete in Christ. The </div><div class="t m22f x11 h4 y20fc ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">good work begun will be finished; the holy thoughts, heavenly affections, and </div><div class="t m244a x99 h5f y22bb ff4 fs13 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">{</div><div class="t m1d0 x79 h4 y1a86 ff4 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">21] </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
